<div class="faq">
  <h2>Why am I seeing this?</h2>

  <p>
    <a href="https://rawgit.com/">RawGit</a> is a free service that makes it easy to load source code directly from GitHub. The <code>{{config.devDomain}}</code> domain is meant to be used for testing and development, and as such it imposes traffic limits. The <code>{{config.cdnDomain}}</code> domain is intended for production use, and has no traffic limits. Both are completely free to use.
  </p>

  <p>
    The site that sent you here is sending too much traffic to <code>{{config.devDomain}}</code>, which probably means they accidentally forgot to switch to <code>{{config.cdnDomain}}</code> in production.
  </p>

  <h2>How can I fix this?</h2>

  <p>
    If you're the owner of the site that generated this request, replace any <code>{{config.devDomain}}</code> URLs on your site with <code>{{config.cdnDomain}}</code> URLs.
  </p>

  <table>
    <tr>
      <th scope="row">Bad:</th>
      <td><code>{{devUrl}}</code></td>
    </tr>

    <tr>
      <th scope="row">Good:</th>
      <td><code>{{cdnUrl}}</code></td>
    </tr>
  </table>

  <p>
    If you're just a visitor, please try to contact the owner of the site that sent you here and give them the information on this page.
  </p>

  <h2>I can't believe you're blocking this site! You're a bad person, etc.</h2>

  <p>
    RawGit is a free service that I operate using my own money. Excessive traffic to <code>{{config.devDomain}}</code> costs me money. I have a good job, but I'm not rich. I have to draw the line somewhere. If this makes you angry, please don't use RawGit.
  </p>

  <p>
    The bandwidth for <code>{{config.cdnDomain}}</code> is generously donated by StackPath, which is why that domain has no traffic limits. If you expect to generate large amounts of traffic, you should use <code>{{config.cdnDomain}}</code>.
  </p>
</div>
